Please spare me your secrets—let the hush be complete;
I’d rather not wander where shadows compete.
What blooms in the silence may wilt in the air;
Not all that is hidden is meant to be shared.

Like stones in a river, some truths lie below—
A shimmer, a flicker, in currents that flow.
I’m content with the ripples, with questions unasked;
Let the weight of your burden remain gently masked.

So keep safe your chambers, don’t force open the door;
Not every mystery’s meant to explore.
Please spare me your secrets—let’s savor the art
Of knowing just enough, while still guarding the heart.

Sharp is the night, but stars with frost alive
Crown the black heavens with their wintry flame;
On silent fields, the icy shadows thrive,
And breath becomes a whisper of your name.

The cold’s precision carves the world anew,
Yet overhead, those glimmering lights delight;
Courage kindles beneath the silver blue,
As hope finds shape in watching through the night.

Oh, let the darkness shimmer, keen and vast;
Let frost-fed stars remind us this will pass.
